annotation.TEXT: But, now that I've seen the level once, maybe Reimu can clear it on her first try... (Also, I'll note this level's BGM a second time since it got cutoff the first time.)
BGM: RoboWarrior - Main Theme
BGM: Diddy Kong Racing - Star City
But, aside from needing to react quickly at the start of this level, it's not very difficult. Once the bombs are all gone, carefully climb up and hit the MOOOONNN!!! to finish.
Sanae demos: 4
CAUTION: Bounce on all of the Utsuhos (which are Dino-Rhinos) twice to clear the level.
Also, make sure you'll land on a cement block after you take out the last one!

Anyways, the upside-down drip blocks turn off the swimming effect, as you can see. Now, you don't want to go straight for the goal sphere immediately, or you'll be Kaizo trapped by the death blocks below.
Oh, I remember this one from Goron50's videos. Hit the ON/OFF block and be ready to act fast!
Whoa, there's so many sprites it's causing slowdown! Anyway, make your way up to the green star, which shouldn't be too difficult, even if the game wasn't lagging.
Oh, hey there Nitoris! How's it going? I see that Nitori has taken up the role of Charles in Charge in this hack.
BGM: Cave Story - Mimiga Village
Be careful about going off screen, too. It might be a good idea to just jump straight up into the left arrow so you know where you'll be on the X axis.
If you aren't too reckless, this level isn't too difficult. Just be careful of their jumps when they run into a block or a wall, and don't let them surprise you or crush you against a ceiling.
Oh, yeah, that's real fair. Unless you've seen this level before or can react in less than one-twentieth of a second, you're gonna die on your first try. Period.

Fortunately, the victory fanfare will make you immune to the spiky things. Also, nice touch with using a song named Nuclear Fusion for a level that contains Utsuhos! (So, if they thought of that, why didn't they put that earlier Cirno level on level 9?)
Ooh, look at all the Nazrins, and the goal is to squash every one of them! They kind of act like the Fly enemies from Super Mario Land.
Hello, and welcome back to Hakurei Adventure Mission! It's been decided that I'm going to continue playing these levels in a nice, orderly fashion.
Oh, man. Cheepo Alices! This one is tough. Can I clear it on my first try?
Uh, oh. Watch out! Those 9-bombs (or e-bombs, if they're facing right) are gonna try to blow you away!
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Nuclear Fusion
Why did I jump there? Well, whatever. Not a big deal.
Ooh, Sanae starts this level on a green star, which turns her fiery! Fry these black blocks to destroy them, but be careful, as some of them contain pointy things!
Okay, now for level 11. Let's try not to accidentally glitch-clear this one!
BGM: SMB3 - Athletic
BGM: Csikos Post
Now for level 17. Oh, and even though Reimu cleared her previous level fiery, it's not going to be of any help, because nearly every level starts you on one of those "shrinker" blocks.

So, that's 20 levels done, and there's 50 main levels remaining, and also the 9 levels on the other side of the Yukari gap, and some palm tree levels going around the main map, which I've been revealing paths for.
BGM: Final Fantasy 7 - J-E-N-O-V-A
Okay, now for level 13... Wait, did I just make a path to that palm tree over there with pink octagons?
The moon clear tile is just like the goal sphere, except it doesn't produce victory music.
Reimu, you've gotta get in there and get revenge for what they did to Sanae!
Okay, this level contains some special blocks. The water drop blocks above the start point cause me to start swimming, and... what do these yellow circle blocks do?
Well, there's another palm tree up there, and it looks like I can reach the one in the upper-left right now as well.
BGM: Ninja Gaiden 2 NES - Act 3-2
To be continued...
Die, all of you, you cheatin' rats!
Level 15...
Doing good so far... That top-center area was the toughest part I think.
I had just 9 seconds left there. I was kind of pushing it a bit.
I wonder where that winding path at the top-center leads, but I'm sure I'll find out eventually.
First, hit the ON/OFF block, then go for the goal sphere. At least this level is pretty easy even if you don't break it with a glitch by accident!
Huh. It looks like I unlocked a special level of some sort. Have I unlocked any others around the map?
So, next time, I'll resume with level 20... Which is actually over here on the far right for some reason. I wonder how long Reimu will stay demo-less, and how many more times Sanae will get gypped...

Oh, what?! I hate that glitch, how you can be hurt just by landing on two stompable enemies at the same time, because technically, you're now moving upwards when the game checks for your collision with the second enemy. Sanae got gypped!
To clear this level, destroy all of the enemies. Shouldn't be too hard, assuming you didn't waste too much time on the lower half of the level.
Yes! And, as a bonus, you'll probably stomp a few Alices during the victory march!
Wah! Umm... They allow me to break the level, I guess! LOL!
Easy, right? There are plenty of harder levels than this in this hack, though.
Well, with the second row of ten levels done, this looks like a good point to take a break.
Okay, good. I made sure to stomp them one at a time there so that they couldn't cheat me again like that.
Wow, I got lucky dodging those Ayas there, though the lag probably helped me. Wait, why was there lag with only five enemies?
Alright, Sanae, show us how this level is meant to work.
If, for some silly reason, you get hit after reaching the green star, just go back to the green star again to regain your firepower.
Level 14...
Level 18...
BGM: Super Nazo Puyo: Ruru no Ruu - Area 5 - Arle vs. Rulue
Once you reach the green star, imitate Flame Hyenard, and BURN THEM ALL TO THE GROUND!!! WOO! TRI-FORMATION!
Oh, and DO NOT spin jump on the lowest Remilia, as you need to bounce back up after stomping that one! You can spin jump on the other four no problem, though.
And there's another one over there. Well, I'll worry about those levels later. For right now, let's just stick to the current course.
BGM: Lufia 2: Rise of the Sinistrals - The Prophet
Okay, Sanae, you're up. Take down level 12 for us, will ya?
Come on, get over here where I can more confidently attack you!
Okay, maybe Sanae will have better luck with level 19...
Shouldn't be too tricky, but just be careful of how the Nazrins on the middle ledges can drop down.
As for the ones on the top, if you lure them to one side then quickly climb up the other, it should be no problem.
Done! That wasn't so hard.
In this one, stomp all of the Remilias, and either destroy them or get them to fall off screen.
Sanae demos: 3
I wonder if those bouncy blocks are meant to just be annoying, or maybe kill you by slamming you into a wall...
Will level 16 be one of those harder levels?
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Nuclear Fusion
Okay, that was definitely not the intended solution, obviously. I think I'm going to properly replay this level.
So, let's continue with level 10.

Okay, now to be fair, I'm going to quickly reenter then Start+Select out of that level just to pass the turn to Sanae, since she's supposed to take on level 11 next, but used up her turn repeating level 10 properly after Reimu glitch-cleared it.
Oh, and once the path is opened, don't concern yourself with preserving your power up, because those upside-down star blocks will force you to become small anyway.
Ow. Fortunately, if you get hurt, you can just touch the green star to power up again, so don't worry too much about revealing those spiky guys.
Who knows, but this level was definitely a more difficult one, and I'm glad I cleared it on my first attempt!
